Of the events of his life very little is known. He married the daughter os Agricola in the year nn. 78 (Chap. IX.), and it hasbeen conjectured that he was a member of his military family during his administration of Aquitania the three previous years. He was praetor nn. 88, and was afterwards absent from Rome for four years, during which period his father-in-law died, no. 93 (Chap. XLV.). He was consul under Nerva, nn. 97. We learn from several passages in Pliny that he was a distin- guished lawyer and orator, as well as historiari.
